article.headline: Massachusetts 72, Savannah State 49
article.story: SAVANNAH, Ga. (AP) -- Rashaun Freeman hit a layup 11 seconds into the game, and Massachusetts never trailed en route to a 72-49 victory over Savannah State Tuesday night. Freeman had 14 points and seven rebounds to lead the Minutemen (6-1) in a balanced attack with four players in double figures. James Life had 13 points and Gary Forbes and Brandon Thomas scored 10 apiece. Savannah State (5-4), which won its first five and has lost four in a row since, was led by Joseph Flegler's 12 points. Javon Randolph was held to 10, including 0-for-5 from 3-point range. The Tigers shot just 31.7 percent, compared to 44.4 for Massachusetts, which rolled to a 42-24 lead at intermission and led by as many as 31 points, 58-27, after a layup by Life at 14:29 of the second half.
